^-{          Trump - Your Most Important Suit          }
^-|fp||cp||AT|
^B@2^*BMM: ^*NMr. Bergen's audio visual lesson covering "Trump Your Most Important Suit" has an excellent introduction which we will bring a summary of. |
PG| ***** 1 ***** |


cp|8|AT|

^B@2^*BMarty Bergen: ^*N|cp||at|Trump - your most important suit. Every time you play in a suit contract, although your trump may not be your strongest suit and it may not be your longest suit, without question it is your most important suit. How you handle trump will often make or break you. There are so many ways that trump can be the key to your success. |
PG| ***** 2 ***** |


AT|

Sometimes you have a hand where all you need to do is draw trump and then enjoy your winners in the other suits. Please keep in mind those hands are rare. ^*BThe vast majority of the time, I would say as high as 60%, you should not be drawing trump first. Your trump can be so helpful in so many ways. You can be ruffing losers. You can be setting up a suit. You can be using your trump as entries to get where you want when you want.^*N|
PG| ***** 3 ***** |


AT|

^B@2^*BMM: I cannot match the mastery by Howard in making the Audio Visual. However, I do my best to recreate at least one board for you. Please click on and have fun. ^*N|
