NT||lb|*mWhich hand do you win the lead?^North~South^2|cp|8|AT|^b@2
^*BMarty Bergen: ^*N|cp||at|You win the club lead in the South hand, saving North's @CA for later as an entry. When the opponents lead a suit and you can win it in either hand, the important consideration is "Where will I need to be later?" as opposed to "^*BWhere must I be right now?^*N". |
